The paper introduces a probabilistic auto-encoder for learning joint distributions over observations and latent variables, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the design principles of the proposed method, which involves low divergence, high mutual information, and low marginal entropy, indicating a focus on information theory and probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IT (Information Theory), which are all relevant to the paper's content.
